author: CNN
description: US Rep. Jasmine Crockett filed Monday to run for US Senate from Texas in 2026, entering the race on the same day that a potential rival, Colin Allred, ended his bid. Crockett, the 44-year-old congresswoman who’s drawn national attention for her criticisms of President Donald Trump, posted a video on her social media account in which she says nothing. She looks off screen as Trump’s voice can be heard insulting her and calling her a “very low IQ person,” then turns to the camera and smiles. The video then cuts off with the message, “Crockett for US Senate.” #CNN #News
title: Jasmine Crockett launches Senate bid from Texas

author: CNN
description: US Rep. Jasmine Crockett filed to run for US Senate from Texas in 2026, entering the race on the same day that a potential rival, Colin Allred, ended his bid. CNN's Dana Bash explains how the shakeup follows several developments that have changed the political calculus heading into next year’s midterm elections.
title: Jasmine Crockett launches Senate bid from Texas

author: CNN
description:
The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention's Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices voted Friday to abandon universal hepatitis B vaccination for newborns, a shift in US immunization policy that experts say will lead to increased illness.

CNN's Pamela Brown speaks with Dr. Joe Hibbeln, member of the CDC Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices. #CNN #News
title: Many parents confused after CDC advisers vote against universal hepatitis B shots for newborns

description: One inmate is still on the run after a brazen escape from a Louisiana jail last week. One of the inmates surrendered and another fatally shot himself as police surrounded a home. CNN's Brynn Gingras reports. #cnn #news
title: Inmate on the run after escaping from Louisiana jail

author: CNN
description: The Indiana House approved a new congressional map designed to hand Republicans all nine of the state’s US House seats, setting the stage for a showdown in the state Senate. At least 10 senators publicly oppose a mid-decade overhaul of the state’s congressional boundaries, and Senate President Pro Tempore Rodric Bray previously insisted he doesn’t have enough votes to pass them.  #CNN #News
title: Trump promises to help oust Republicans who oppose redistricting plan

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Jomana Karadsheh reflects one year after her exclusive interview with Abu Mohammad al-Jolani, then the militant leader of the Syrian group Hayat Tahrir al-Sham (HTS). Shortly afterward, he became the Syrian leader following the fall of President Bashar al-Assad and became known as Ahmed al-Sharaa. #CNN #news
title: CNN looks back on interview with Syrian leader one year on

author: CNN
description: The high court appears ready to side with President Donald Trump on the firing of a member of the Federal Trade Commission and give him more control of the government. During oral arguments today, liberals warned that backing Trump could “destroy the structure of government” as conservatives tried to tamp down fears.  #CNN #News
title: Supreme Court appears ready to side with Trump on firing FTC commissioner

author: CNN
description:
Paramount has gone straight to Warner Bros. Discovery’s shareholders with an all-cash offer in an extraordinary endeavor to gain control of Hollywood’s most sought-after prize – a bid that Netflix beat on Friday. Paramount was widely expected to be the frontrunner for Warner Bros., but WBD opted instead for Netflix, which it said offered a more lucrative deal. Paramount offered $30 per share in an all-cash deal for the entire company, while Netflix offered $27.75 for Warner Bros. and HBO — $23.25 per share in cash and $4.50 in stock.

Warner Bros. Discovery is the parent company of CNN.

CNN chief media analyst Brian Stelter reports, and Dana Bash speaks with Puck founding partner William Cohan. #CNN #News
title: Paramount launches hostile takeover bid for Warner Bros. Discovery

author: CNN
description: A magnitude-7.6 earthquake struck around 44 miles off the coast of northeastern Japan, triggering a tsunami warning. CNN's Hanako Montgomery felt tremors all the way in Tokyo.

author: CNN
description:
Top bipartisan lawmakers who were briefed last week on a September “double-tap” strike on an alleged drug boat in the Caribbean say they would support the release of video from the attack, with some Democratic lawmakers actively calling for it to be made public.

CNN correspondent Arlette Saenz reports from Capitol Hill, Pamela Brown speaks with Rep. Joaquin Castro (D-TX) and Kate Bolduan speaks with Rep. Gabe Vasquez (D-NM), who sits on the House Armed Services Committee. #CNN #News
title: Amid bipartisan pressure, Hegseth 'reviewing' release of video of second boat strike

author: CNN
description: A tsunami warning has been issued for parts of Japan’s northeastern coast after a magnitude-7.6 earthquake struck off the coastline Monday, according to Japan’s Meteorological Agency (JMA). CNN's Hanako Montgomery reports from Tokyo. #CNN #News
title: Tsunami alert issued for Japan after 7.6-magnitude earthquake

author: CNN
description: Five years after her dog Choco went missing, Patricia got a call she wasn’t expecting. He had been found in Lincoln, Michigan, 2000 miles away from his home in Sacramento, California. Thanks to the help of volunteers, Choco has now been returned to his rightful owners.
title: Missing dog returns home after five years

author: CNN
description:
Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has arrived in London for a meeting with European leaders at Downing Street. He is expected in Brussels and Rome later after talks in Florida between US and Ukrainian negotiators came to a halt Saturday with no breakthrough, according to Ukrainian officials. The summit comes after US President Donald Trump claimed Zelensky had not yet read the latest US proposal to end the war, adding he was a “little disappointed” in the Ukrainian leader.

CNN's Clare Sebastian reports from London, CNN's Alayna Treene reports from the White House and CNN's Sara Sidner speaks with Rep. Lloyd Doggett (D-TX). #CNN #News
title: Donald Trump, Jr. says President Trump may walk away from peace talks

description: President Donald Trump took center stage at the Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts on Sunday evening to pay tribute to the newest class of honorees. Trump was elected chairman of the Kennedy Center board after he removed Democratic-appointed trustees and installed a small cadre of loyalists in their stead. #cnn #trump #kennedycenter
